													At the beginning of each school year, there are many papers to be signed.
I agree I have (1) read the student handbook, (2) health forms, (3) appropriate use of technology at school, (4) photos of my children for promotional purposes, and so on.
Then, this year out of the blue, a new consent shows up — a consent to record classes for operational purposes — and if I don’t sign it, it will significantly impact my child’s education.
Wait … what? 
This doesn’t sound right. What exactly are opera...
